      • CreateInstance

        public static <T extends Structure> T CreateInstance(java.lang.String resourceLocation,
                                                     java.lang.Class<? extends Structure> child)
        Creates an instance of the structure after reading from a resource location and converting it from JSON.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type which extends Structure.
        Parameters:
        resourceLocation - The location of the JSON file to load. Example: "assets/prefab/structures/warehouse.json"
        child - The child class which extends Structure.
        Returns:
        Null if the resource wasn't found or the JSON could not be parsed, otherwise the de-serialized object.

      • BuildStructure

        public boolean BuildStructure(StructureConfiguration configuration,
                              net.minecraft.world.World world,
                              net.minecraft.util.math.BlockPos originalPos,
                              net.minecraft.util.EnumFacing assumedNorth,
                              net.minecraft.entity.player.EntityPlayer player)
        This is the main building method for this structure.
        Parameters:
        configuration - The configuration the user updated.
        world - The current world.
        originalPos - The block the user clicked on.
        assumedNorth - This should always be "NORTH" when the file is based on a scan.
        player - The player requesting the structure.
        Returns:
        True if the build can occur, otherwise false.

      • BeforeBuilding

        protected boolean BeforeBuilding(StructureConfiguration configuration,
                                 net.minecraft.world.World world,
                                 net.minecraft.util.math.BlockPos originalPos,
                                 net.minecraft.util.EnumFacing assumedNorth,
                                 net.minecraft.entity.player.EntityPlayer player)
        This method is used before any building occurs to check for things or possibly pre-build locations. Note: This is even done before blocks are cleared.
        Parameters:
        configuration - The structure configuration.
        world - The current world.
        originalPos - The original position clicked on.
        assumedNorth - The assumed northern direction.
        player - The player which initiated the construction.
        Returns:
        False if processing should continue, otherwise true to cancel processing.
